company: CASE - Consent Awareness & Sexual Education Club
title: Vice President - Communications
description: The Consent Awareness and Sexual Education Club is a feminist anti-racist club at the University of Calgary that seeks to educate young Calgarians about consent as a means of sexual assault prevention. We believe that preventative measures focusing on potential perpetrators are more effective than preventative measures focusing on potential victims. We hope to educate the public as well as University of Calgary students about what consent is \u2013 and help foster an environment where consent is requested and respected in sexual relationships. Specifically, we will advocate for consent education in Calgary Junior High Schools and create consent awareness campaigns at the University of Calgary.

title: Lead Hands On Car Care
description: Car Care Clinic and Financial Education Program (specifically made accessible for low income individuals). I eagerly volunteered to lead this weekend program that was designed to help people understand the basics of how their cars function, its components, and how those parts work together (with maintenance and repair) to keep their car on the road safely. Their own cars would be brought into the shop and given a free inspection to help make practical and immediate sense of what we were teaching. In developing the curriculum for this program I felt strongly that a practical approach would appeal to participants and so in addition to the course outline and slide decks, I created a series of real-world interactive displays. As an example I cut apart a number of suspension components, pulled out wiring harnesses and meticulously labelled and displayed them.  Being able to actually handle these components and seeing firsthand how they interact was a revelation to most of the students and their praise spoke to it's effectiveness in helping to make sense of a plethora of otherwise confusing parts.

description: \u2022\tSecretary, 2020 - present\u2022\tChair,  Fundraising Committee,  2017 - present\u2022\tChair, Special Events Committee, 2017 - present\u2022\tChair, Membership Committee,  2016 - presentThe Thunder Bay Historical Museum Society was created in 1908 to preserve and interpret the history of Northwestern Ontario through lectures, publications, the erection of monuments and plaques, and the preservation of documents. The Society\u2019s mandate has always been to serve both the city and district of Thunder Bay in Northwestern Ontario, Canada, and to preserve the history of the entire region. Today an active, efficient organization has assumed responsibilities far beyond those undertaken by its founders. The Society operates as a museum, an archives, and a historical society, and offers a wide range of programs and services in each area. Through its exhibits, publications, collections, and programs, the Thunder Bay Museum will engage with the people of Thunder Bay and Northwestern Ontario in a spirit of openness and universal access as well as trust, freedom of expression, and debate. Our motto, \u201cLearning Though History,\u201d reveals our fundamental commitment to education and a dedication to the idea of a community in which citizens enjoy equal opportunity to participate in public life, culture, and an exploration of our collective past.

title: Social Media Coordinator
description: Founded in 1905, The Champlain Society works to echo the voices of some of Canada\u2019s most eloquent citizens. Since the early 1600s, explorers, merchants, public servants, scientists, ordinary people, and extraordinary men and women have left riveting accounts of their actions and thoughts. Through its books and Digital Collection, its blog and its podcasts, the Champlain Society makes the adventures, explorations, discoveries, and opinions that have shaped Canada available to all who have an interest in its past. The Champlain Society is accessible, but it is uncompromisingly scholarly: its works are the object of meticulous treatment by specialists whose role has been to highlight the significance of the eyewitness accounts and to inform readers of the context in which these documents were drafted.The mission of The Champlain Society is to increase public awareness of, and accessibility to, Canada\u2019s rich store of historical records.

title: Equipier secouriste b\u00e9n\u00e9vole
description: J'ai rejoint la Croix Rouge Fran\u00e7aise de Paris en tant que b\u00e9n\u00e9vole fin 2010, d'abord en m'engageant au sein de l'\u00e9quipe de l'Action Sociale. Je participe aux maraudes, sorties v\u00e9hicul\u00e9es au sein d'un arrondissement pour partir \u00e0 la rencontre des b\u00e9n\u00e9ficiaires afin de les soutenir gr\u00e2ce \u00e0 des produits de premi\u00e8re n\u00e9cessit\u00e9 (alimentaire, v\u00eatements, hygi\u00e8ne), de les aider dans leurs d\u00e9marches administratives, mais surtout pour pr\u00e9server le lien social en \u00e9changeant quelques mots autour d'un caf\u00e9.Apr\u00e8s plusieurs mois, j'ai d\u00e9cid\u00e9 de renforcer mon engagement en entamant les formations de secourisme. D'abord grand public (PSC1/AFPS), puis dipl\u00f4me d'\u00e9tat (PSE1 puis PSE2). Je suis alors devenu \u00e9quipier secouriste fin 2011. Au sein d'une ambulance de la Croix Rouge Fran\u00e7aise, nous assurons des gardes pour la Brigade des Sapeurs-Pompiers de Paris (BSPP) ainsi que pour le SAMU de Paris.C'est avec un engagement \"administratif\" que j'ai compl\u00e9t\u00e9 mon b\u00e9n\u00e9volat fin 2012 en devenant cadre de direction dans l'unit\u00e9 locale des 3e et 10e arrondissements de Paris. En tant que responsable mission, mon r\u00f4le \u00e9tait de assurer le planning, la couverture des diff\u00e9rentes missions de secours ainsi que la r\u00e9ponse op\u00e9rationnelle des secouriste b\u00e9n\u00e9voles de l'arrondissement.

company: The The Equestrian Secular and Chapterial Order of St. Joachim
title: Knight
description: The Equestrian, Secular and Chapterial Order of Saint Joachim was established on the 20th of June, 1755 in Leitmeritz, Bohemia by fourteen nobles and distinguished military leaders of the Holy Roman Empire. Having seen the terrible consequences of ongoing religious wars in Europe, our founders dedicated themselves to \u201cworship the Supreme Being, show tolerance towards all religions, loyalty towards their princes, support the needs of their military, the poor, widows and orphans.\u201d The Order was uniquely composed of both Protestant and Catholic nobles and leaders at a time when religion violently divided Europe and the German states within the Holy Roman Empire, and other knightly orders allied themselves exclusively as defenders of one faith or the other.Today the Order supports its original mission of tolerance by being one of the most inclusive Orders in the world. In addition to religious tolerance, whereby persons of any faith can be admitted as a member of the Order, it has extended that mission of tolerance to a broader socially progressive mandate and welcomes individuals regardless of faith, gender, race, nationality, class or sexual orientation. It stands resolutely opposed to sectarian violence and religious extremism in any form. With Commanderies in four countries and members all over the world, The Order of Saint Joachim continues its charitable mission through men and women who embrace its original chivalric virtues.

We now encourage you to activate your membership in the Kentucky Colonels by making a tax-deductible contribution to the Good Works Program.Kentucky Colonels are unwavering in devotion to faith, family, commonwealth, and country. Passionate about being compassionate. Proud leaders who are gentle but strong in will and commitment. The generosity of our members enables the Kentucky Colonels \u2013 as a recognized 501 (c) (3) tax exempt nonprofit organization \u2013 to reach out and care for our children, support those in need, and preserve our rich heritage.

description: Created in the fall of 2012, The Bishop\u2019s University Gender Equity Centre\u2019s impressive campaign against sexual assault No means KNOW has spread across Quebec and Ontario.No means KNOW focuses on sexual assault awareness, consent, rape culture, and alcohol related sexual assault. The campaign\u2019s aims are threefold:1-to deconstruct taboos surrounding sex and assault, by creating a space in which dialogue about such issues is encouraged in a comfortable atmosphere2-to inform and educate the community through public scholarship3-to initiate change in the way in which sexual assault and abuse survivors are perceived, and in how sexuality is approached in relation to violenceMost sexual assault campaigns target potential victims, by urging women to restrict and monitor their own behavior \u2013 in essence, how not to be assaulted. Research has shown that this is not only ineffective, but also contributes to delayed recovery after attacks, as the victims are taught to blame themselves instead of their attacker. No means KNOW offers a radical change in the way we view sexual assault, by focusing on educating potential offenders and bystanders rather than potential victims.

title: Vice President
description: CEG was created in the mid-1970\u2019s to meet the needs of smaller exploration and production companies \u2013 those not eligible for membership in the larger compensation and benefit associations, due to their size or lack of full- time HR professionals. Today, CEG has grown to include member companies with a varied number of employees, but continues to maintain a focus on the Western Canadian E&P market segment, allowing members to share information on many aspects of Human Resources Management.CEG is an association through which company representatives can discuss subjects that include compensation and benefits, labour legislation changes, labour relations, trends in employment policies, training and development concepts, and occupational health & safety issues in the Western Canadian energy industry. We are a group of companies that share common objectives and meet six times per year in pursuit of them. We are a not for profit, informal organization and therefore do not have a charter.In addition to the camaraderie that member companies\u2019 representatives enjoy during the luncheon meetings, we develop candid and confidential relationships for sharing relevant information. Most information is exchanged by member surveys, which includes interpretation or clarification of industry survey data relating to compensation and benefits, legislation and other issues.

title: President
description: CEG was created in the mid-1970\u2019s to meet the needs of smaller exploration and production companies \u2013 those not eligible for membership in the larger compensation and benefit associations, due to their size or lack of full- time HR professionals. Today, CEG has grown to include member companies with a varied number of employees, but continues to maintain a focus on the Western Canadian E&P market segment, allowing members to share information on many aspects of Human Resources Management.CEG is an association through which company representatives can discuss subjects that include compensation and benefits, labour legislation changes, labour relations, trends in employment policies, training and development concepts, and occupational health & safety issues in the Western Canadian energy industry. We are a group of companies that share common objectives and meet six times per year in pursuit of them. We are a not for profit, informal organization and therefore do not have a charter.In addition to the camaraderie that member companies\u2019 representatives enjoy during the luncheon meetings, we develop candid and confidential relationships for sharing relevant information. Most information is exchanged by member surveys, which includes interpretation or clarification of industry survey data relating to compensation and benefits, legislation and other issues.

description: One of the best experiences in my life, such a rich and generous one, full of happy memories, sad moments and great achievements.We used to play, sing, read and paint. Chatting with them helped me widen my horizons, it's unbelievable how amazing talking to these little ones could be, I've seriously learnt a lot and at the same time I'm sure that this kind of chats helped them learn how to speak fearlessly.I taught them English and we dug deeper into music all together.The worst part was saying goodbye to these angels who ended up emotionally attached to me, which made me feel guilty at the end, because in such institutions that regularly cycle in and out volunteers, children aren't given the stability and consistency of a regular and familiar caretaker that they need. Instead, they continuously become attached to volunteers who quickly leave them, creating a sense of abandonment and mistrust among children.

there is no money, human resource is a very precious resource.The Freedom Farm is a unique and very important project established by two amazing women. Organizations of this kind, especially in the crucial initiative stages, tend to \"chase their own tail\" and turn off fires, instead of planning ahead and working smartly, due to lack of resources in relation for the many tasks their are to conquer.As for the last past months, I am leading the farm through a process of establishing a volunteer-based organizational structure designed to take the organization to the next level, to enable long term planning and smart execution of plans, and to help it reach its goals.

title: Rescue & Redeliver Surplus Meals
description: Hundreds of volunteers across the country gather each evening to rescue prepared meal surpluses from restaurants, catering companies, corporate cafeterias, banquet halls, shopping malls, bakeries and more.  Fresh food is safely collected and redelivered to nonprofit organizations including soup kitchens, shelters, and community centers serving the needy.This project relies on volunteers to collect donated food and redeliver it to nonprofit organizations serving the needy.  Volunteers are trained on-site over a period of a week so food establishments become familiar with the volunteer and the volunteer's private vehicle.  For late evening pick-ups, including from celebratory banquet halls, volunteers may be asked to transfer the collected food directly to nonprofit associations and soup kitchens or to transport it to a temporary refrigerated storage room of the organization.Volunteering is suitable for individuals or groups of up to three people in each activity. There is a need for a private car to travel to and from each food establishment and the beneficiary nonprofits.  Short-term and  long-term assignments are both possible, with most evening collection activities requiring about an hour and a half.

title: Board Member
description: CMT Israel is the first established (RA) Organization in Israel for CMT patients and families.\u200bCHARCOT MARIE TOOTH (CMT) - This is a progressive genetic neurological disease that causes damage to the peripheral nervous system, resulting in difficulties in the functioning of the feet and palms. The disease is divided into more than 100 different types and there are even types that have not yet been diagnosed. The range of severity ranges from walking with a slight limp to severely disabled patients who move in a wheelchair and suffer from severe pain.\u200bThe association focuses on creating a supportive community for CMT patients and their families, promoting research to find a cure for the disease, establishing centers of diagnosis and treatment in Israel, and raising awareness among the general public about the existence of the disease.\u200bThe organization's goal is to bring all the relevant information to patients and their families and help them cope with the disease.#cmt#Charcot

title: Co-Founder
description: Pulmonary hypertension is a debilitating illness that can strike children and adults of all ages but most often afflicts women in their childbearing years. The disease affects the blood vessels between the heart and lungs causing a drop in oxygen levels and injuring the right side of the heart muscle.  Women stricken with the illness are unable to function normally. They have difficulty walking from one room the next, climbing stairs or otherwise conducting their daily affairs.The Israel Pulmonary Hypertension Association, a subsidiary of Europe Hypertension Association , was established in 2000 in order to assist and support people suffering from the disease.  The organization's objectives include:Providing financial assistance to patients for the purchase of medications and medical equipment,Advocacy leading to the inclusion of medications and new treatments in the government's basket of subsidized drugs and health services,Gathering relevant information concerning the disease and disseminating it to patients and their families,Operating a website offering information on a broad array of topics relating to the disease,Organizing support groups for patients and their families,Convening yearly conferences including lectures by physicians and other specialists,Providing a framework for social interaction and mutual support and sponsoring social events for patients and their families.http://www.phisrael.org.il/content_eng.asp?type=98
